<h3> Run the content export </h3>

<p>This content migrator tool allows you to migrate content from old plone or zope sites
 to current plone</p>

<p>The export tab will export content to a generic setup style plain text RFC282 format or XML format, either of which contain all metadata and can be imported into another CMS.<br />
HTML format is for a browsable static dump - such as a crawler would generate. But it doesn't contain all metadata, and is not re-importable.<br />
NB: The export tool can be installed independently as a Product in an old site by dropping the 
ContentMigrator folder from the ilrt.contentmigrator egg into its Products directory.</p>

<form action="manage_runExport" method="post">
<fieldset>
<label>Export all content in the following folder (default is the portal root)</label> 
 <br /><input type="text" name="root" value="/" />
<label><input type="checkbox" name="exportusers" value="yes" /> Export all users</label> 
<label>
<input type="radio" name="format" value="CSV" checked="checked" /> CSV
<input type="radio" name="format" value="XML" /> XML
<input type="radio" name="format" value="HTML" /> HTML (export only)
</label> 
 <input type="submit" value=" Export content " />
</fieldset>
</form>

<tal:getout tal:define="out here/getLog | nothing">
<ol tal:condition="out | nothing">
 <li tal:repeat="item out"><span tal:replace="item" /></li>
</ol>
</tal:getout>

